item.title: CVE-2022-4447|2024-08-03T01:41:44.594Z -- unknown -- fontsy
item.description: The Fontsy WordPress plugin through 1.8.6 does not properly sanitize and escape a parameter before using it in a SQL statement via an AJAX action available to unauthenticated users, leading to a SQL injection.
